<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100235580240394></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100235580240394><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2653&mid=100235580240394>RE: Great item for ENC!</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2653&mid=100235580240394#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=68393><span id=Scholar>Northerner</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>64 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 6th 4:10 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.23]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Indeed it is a nice Enchanter item.  Still, I feel forced to debunk the myth of wisdom for successes in tradeskills.  It is the higher of Wisdom OR Intelligence that determines your skill raises in any tradeskill.  Your skill in that tradeskill determines success combined with the higher of the two again, not with wisdom as is often said.  At least that is what I have gleaned from EQTRADERS.com, a definitive source for information I believe.<br><br>cheers,<br>Celeris (me)<br>Faeril (my retired Brewer, Baker, Potter, Tailor and part-time Smith)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
