<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99305518286608></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99305518286608><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2653&mid=99305518286608>Actually pretty decent item</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2653&mid=99305518286608#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 20th 12:39 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's actually a pretty good item - and here's why<br><br>Most chanters able to get this should be at the point of having 200int or more already, but we always want more of 2 things: CHA and Mana. <br><br>So this little cup lets you chop down some of the unused int (which is easy to make up elsewhere) and gain 5 CHA and also 25mana. <br><br>At the high levels it's all about juggling stats if you know what you're doing. Keeping Int at 200 while maxing out as much CHA and mana as possible...<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
